To find total running time of any vasp job
When there are multiple OUTCAR files in named folders (1, 2, 3,...). 
It can grep "Total CPU time" from each file and display on screen in order


Input
________
multiple folders of vasp jobs, each contains OUTCAR file.
change ncell value according to your number of folders. 



Process
_________
./grep.sh



Output
________
 Total CPU time used (sec):      190.176
 Total CPU time used (sec):      224.664
 Total CPU time used (sec):      190.176
 Total CPU time used (sec):      224.664
 ...


if there is any problem to run grep.sh, use this command 
chmod 777 grep.sh
and then run again
